Javier Hernandez's strike for Mexico helped seal his country's place in the last 16 of the World Cup - as well as giving the forward a welcome boost of confidence.

The 25-year-old endured a frustrating season at Manchester United under David Moyes and his form suffered as a result.

But Hernandez's goal after coming on as a substitute contributed to Mexico's 3-1 win over Croatia, a victory which set-up a second round tie with Louis van Gaal's Holland.

