Van Persie has bagged three World Cup goals already but he sat out Holland's 2-0 victory over Chile after picking up a yellow card in each of his first two matches.

Hernandez said: 'It will be a joy.

'He is a team-mate with whom I've experienced two important years.

'I've learned a lot from him, we won a title and it will be very nice to see him again.'

